o by.</p><p>Willy Caballero could start between the sticks with Antonio Rudiger returning, but other than that their defensive setup could remain untouched. Besides that we could see Kenedy, Ampadu, Musonda, and Batshuayi brought in, but none of them should have an impact in the defensive aspect.</p><p>Bournemouth, on the other hand, are likely to be playing a full strength squad as they hunt for some unlikely silverware this season. Eddie Howe could opt for some changes though, especially after seeing his side hammered 4-0 at home to Liverpool on Sunday.</p><p>The Cherries are now winless in six matches in all competitions and find themselves struggling a bit, although away from home they tend to be a little tighter at the back. They only conceded one at Manchester United last week and limited Spurs to one as well. Their lack of scoring ability is an issue though, and it has resulted in four of their last six away games seeing fewer than three goals.</p><p>Chelsea have only seen one of their last five at home end with three or more goals as well, but despite this the bookies are expecting a goalfest. This leaves value out there for us, and backing Under 2.5 Goals at this price is fantastic value, along with a tight 1-0 win for the hosts.</p><div class=\"more\"><p><a href=\"/free-football-betting-tips/\">Football predictions</a> including accumulators, both teams to score, both teams to score and win, correct score and 10 to 1,000 challenge!</p></div></div><h2 class=\"preview-dark-heading\">Head To Head</h2><div class=\"text-content\"><p>Chelsea have won four and lost one of their five previous meetings with Bournemouth.</p></div><h2 class=\"preview-dark-heading\">Chelsea vs Bournemouth Stats</h2><div class=\"text-content\"><ul><li>80% of Chelseas last five competitive home games have seen fewer than three goals.</li><li>The Blues have kept a clean sheet in 67% of these matches as well, winning 50% of them 1-0.</li><li>Bournemouth have seen fewer than three goals in